#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""AeroLIT aerolitctl merge-readiness regression test.

Run from the aerolitctl repo root on a test VM.

This is a broad manual smoke/regression test for the work around:
- CLI parsing/help
- provision wrapper behavior
- configure server mode handling
- generated server vars
- status read-only reporting
- deploy server dry-run mode behavior
- show vs dry-run safety behavior
- configure init dry-run behavior
- bundle manifest creation/validation/idempotency behavior
- configure repos discovery/validation/generated-vars behavior
- configure ansible managed inventory/group_vars behavior
- configure pxe managed profile/generated-vars behavior
- configure all orchestration behavior

It intentionally runs real `aerolitctl configure server`,
`aerolitctl configure repos`, `aerolitctl configure ansible`,
`aerolitctl configure pxe`, and `aerolitctl configure init`
commands because those are the only way to confirm saved config,
generated vars, managed Ansible files, and bundle manifest
behavior. By default it restores the original config, state,
generated vars, manifest, sync files, CI file, managed Ansible
files, and managed PXE files before exiting.

Recommended location:
  tools/aerolitctl_merge_readiness.py

Recommended run:
  sudo python3 tools/aerolitctl_merge_readiness.py

If firewalld is not active on future test VM, run:
  sudo python3 tools/aerolitctl_merge_readiness.py --no-require-firewalld
"""

